---
import SectionLabel from './SectionLabel.astro';
---

<section id="problem" class="border-t border-b border-rule bg-white py-20 sm:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 sm:px-10">
    <SectionLabel index="01" label="The problem" />
    <h2 class="display mt-8 max-w-2xl text-[2.25rem] leading-[1.05] sm:text-[3rem]">
      Finance gets one invoice a month and <span class="text-accent">nobody</span> can tell them which feature
      wrote it.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-8 max-w-2xl space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
      <p>
        The root cause is that AI spend arrives detached from what caused it. You can't downgrade a model you can't
        trace, or hold a team to a number nobody can attribute to them. Optimizations becomes a guess,
        and guesses don't survive contact with a real bill. 
      </p>
      <p class="font-semibold text-ink">
        We are going to <mark class="rounded bg-accent/15 px-1 text-accent-deep">fix attribution first</mark> and
        the rest stops being mysterious.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 h-[280px] overflow-hidden rounded-lg sm:h-[340px]">
      <img
        src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/5480781/pexels-photo-5480781.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600"
        alt="Server infrastructure running AI workloads"
        class="h-full w-full object-cover"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
